"overall_meaning": "He who moves in a dream, being glorified, is the Self, he said.  This is immortal, fearless, this is Brahman.  With a calm heart, he departed.  Indeed, reaching the gods, he saw this fear: Even though this body becomes blind, he who is without pleasure becomes without pleasure.  If weak, he becomes not weak; this does not deteriorate by fault."
